  "summaries": [
    {
      "id": 23732,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "@tomtenisse identified a vulnerability in Grammarly Keyboard for Android that allowed malicious application installed on the device to guess the PKCE code verifier value and consequently obtain access to OAuth access_token (`grauth` cookie). The vulnerability was fixed by moving from PRNG to `SecureRandom`\n\nThank you, @tomtenisse, for the detailed report and collaboration!",
